// Portfolio Modal 3
#portfolioModal3.portfolio-modal.modal.fade(tabindex='-1', aria-labelledby='portfolioModal3', aria-hidden='true')
    .modal-dialog.modal-xl
        .modal-content
            .modal-header.border-0
                button.btn-close(type='button', data-bs-dismiss='modal', aria-label='Close')
            .modal-body.text-center.pb-5
                .container
                    .row.justify-content-center
                        .col-lg-8
                            // Portfolio Modal - Title
                            h2.portfolio-modal-title.text-secondary.text-uppercase.mb-0 Multiplayer Statistics Dashboard Website for Battle for Wesnoth
                            // Icon Divider
                            .divider-custom
                                .divider-custom-line
                                .divider-custom-icon
                                    i.fas.fa-microchip
                                .divider-custom-line
                            // Portfolio Modal - Text
                            p.mb-4
                                | I created a dashboard web application for The Battle for Wesnoth, a free turn-based strategy game.                                
                            // Portfolio Modal - Image 1
                            figure
                                a(href='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wesnoth/wesnoth-multiplayer-data-dashboard/main/readme_assets/full_page.png', target='_blank')
                                    img.img-fluid.rounded(src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wesnoth/wesnoth-multiplayer-data-dashboard/main/readme_assets/full_page.png', alt='Screenshot of the Wesnoth Dashboard')
                                figcaption.mb-5
                                    | App Screenshot
                            // View Live App button
                            a.btn.btn-secondary.mb-5(href='https://replays.wesnoth.org/dashboard/', target='_blank')
                                | Visit the Live Application
                                i.fas.fa-external-link-alt.ml-2
                            // Major Technologies Used
                            h3.text-secondary.text-uppercase.mb-3 Technologies Used
                            .d-flex.flex-wrap.justify-content-center.mb-5
                                .d-flex.flex-column.align-items-center.m-3
                                    img.portfolio-modal-technology-img(src='https://pandas.pydata.org/static/img/pandas_mark.svg', alt='Pandas')
                                    p.text-center.mb-0 pandas
                                .d-flex.flex-column.align-items-center.m-3
                                    img.portfolio-modal-technology-img(src='https://chart-studio.plotly.com/static/webapp/images/plotly-logo.8d56a320dbb8.png', alt='Plotly')
                                    p.text-center.mb-0 Plotly Dash
                                .d-flex.flex-column.align-items-center.m-3
                                    img.portfolio-modal-technology-img(src='https://mariadb.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/vertical-logo_black.svg', alt='MariaDB')
                                    p.text-center.mb-0 MariaDB
                                .d-flex.flex-column.align-items-center.m-3
                                    img.portfolio-modal-technology-img(src='https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.0/assets/brand/bootstrap-logo.svg', alt='Bootstrap')
                                    p.text-center.mb-0 Bootstrap                                    
                            // Portfolio Modal - List
                            h3.text-secondary.text-uppercase.mb-3 Details
                            ul.portfolio-modal-list.mb-4
                                li 
                                    | I identified that there was an opportunity to create a dashboard after I saw that there was a monthly
                                    a(href='https://forums.wesnoth.org/viewtopic.php?t=57533') Multiplayer Activity Report
                                    | that was being manually prepared and released. 
                                li I created a proof-of-concept for the Wesnoth organization to interact with before they decided to officially adopt my dashboard.
                                li I communicated with other developers to get access to the database and other data I needed, to setup and deploy to development and production environments, to ask for code reviews, and to address comments and requested changes.
                                li I wrote clear documentation to enable other developers to understand and run the app without having to ask me personally for all the steps in the process. I included links to the official documentation for the various technologies and libraries used by the application.
                                li I wrote tests to help ensure quality and possibly serve as a secondary form of documentation.
                            // Close Modal button
                            button.btn.btn-primary(data-bs-dismiss='modal')
                                i.fas.fa-xmark.fa-fw
                                | Close Window
            .modal-footer.border-0
                p.portfolio-modal-legal-attribution
                    | All logos and trademarks in this page are property of their respective owners.
